title: February 15
description: French president François Hollande flew to Washington this week for a state visit. After a couple of days with the Obamas, he headed to California to pay his respects to the Moses family.

children.title: Hollande
children.description:
The French consulate invited the French citizens of the San Francisco Bay Area for a "Rencontre de la communauté française avec le Président de la République".

It took place at the Hilton hotel near Union Square.

children.title: Marie-Laure
children.description:
The event filled up as soon as the consulate announced it. We didn't manage to snatch tickets in time.

Fortunately for us, our friends Marie-Laure and François ended up with a couple of extra tickets on their hands and generously passed them on to us.

children.title: Les Nguyens
children.description: Marie-Laure and François are both French. Like us, they have been living in the Bay Area for decades. Their kids go to EB.

children.title: Les Moses
children.description: Moses wore a tie for the occasion. He makes a fine French citizen.

children.title: Bain de Foule
children.description: After an uplifting 45 minute speech about the entrepreneurial spirit of the French community in California, François Hollande walked the crowd. Marie-Laure managed to wiggle her way to him for a quick snap shot.

children.title: Jut
children.description: Jut, the start-up where Lucie is working, turned 1 year old this week. These are the four founders: Steve (CEO), Larry (CTO), Mike  (VP Engineering) and Apurva (VP Marketing).  All in all, the company is just 15 people but new folks are joining weekly.

children.title: Sibley
children.description: We went for a hike in Sibley Volcanic Regional Preserve, a park just beyond Tilden. The volcano part of it is not very apparent. It used to be more impressive 10 million years ago. Still, it's a nice area.

children.title: Pooped
children.description: Felix has been a little sick this week. The hike might have been a bit premature. Although it was only 2 miles long, Felix ran out of steam and dragged his feet after 20 minutes. As if by osmosis, Milo's energy deflated in unison.

children.title: Rough Road
children.description: Every 10 minutes we had to stop to let the kids rest for a bit. It was a Rough Road indeed.  The kids did agree that it had the potential to be a nice hike. We vowed to come back here on a weekend Higgsy is staying with us. Dogs are allowed off leash in Sibley.

children.title: Rough Hike
children.description: If the kids are having a hard time hiking, so do the parents. After an hour of "Are we there yet? I am tired. How much longer is it?", we were all glad to get in sight of the parking lot.
